  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[Convergent by comparison with \(\sum 1/n^2\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="0" format="html"><text><![CDATA[Convergent with sum \(\ln(\ln 2)\)]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
  <answer fraction="100" format="html"><text><![CDATA[Divergent (integral test: \(\int_2^\infty\frac{dx}{x\ln x}=\infty\))]]></text><feedback format="html"><text></text></feedback></answer>
</question>
<!-- Q17 --><question type="multichoice">
  <name><text>Series - Necessary Condition</text></name>
  <questiontext format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p>If \(\displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}a_n\) converges, then:</p>]]></text></questiontext>
  <generalfeedback format="html"><text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Answer: (A) \(a_n\to0\)</strong></p><p>Necessary condition for convergence: if \(\sum a_n\) converges, then \(a_n\to0\). The converse is false (harmonic series). This is the divergence test: if \(a_n\not\to0\), the series diverges.</p>]]></text></generalfeedback>
